### Tested versions

- Reproducible in 4.6 (with additional scons flags: ccflags=/guard:cf linkflags=/GUARD:CF)
- Not reproducible in 4.5

### System information

Godot v4.6.mono (28df6834b) - Windows 11 (build 26200) - Multi-window, 2 monitors - Direct3D 12 (Forward+) - dedicated NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4090 (NVIDIA; 32.0.15.7680) - 13th Gen Intel(R) Core(TM) i9-13900K (32 threads) - 127.7 GiB memory

### Issue description

I build a small fork of Godot with the MSVC compiler and Control Flow Guard enabled as required by the polices of my company. I am upgrading our fork from 4.5 to 4.6 and found it crashed immediately in `Hook_GetProcAddress` being called by `dinput8.dll` with the following message:

> Unhandled exception at 0x00007FFBBD7A17E0 (ntdll.dll) in godot.windows.editor.x86_64.mono.exe: Indirect call guard check detected invalid control transfer.

This is related to the following change: #113013

I have verified two possible fixes.

## Possible Fix Option 1
```diff
FARPROC __stdcall Hook_GetProcAddress(HMODULE p_module, LPCSTR p_name) {
	if (String(p_name) == "HidD_GetProductString") {
		return (FARPROC)(LPVOID)Hook_HidD_GetProductString;
	}
-	if (Original_GetProcAddress) {
-		return Original_GetProcAddress(p_module, p_name);
-	}
-	return nullptr;
+	return GetProcAddress(p_module, p_name);
}
```

By calling `GetProcAddress` directly, the hook no longer does an indirect (function pointer) call. At first I thought this might not be OK to call `GetProcAddress` directly rather than what the IAT originally pointed to (`Original_GetProcAddress`), but `Hook_HidD_GetProductString` is doing this with calling `HidD_GetProductString` directly so maybe it is ok?

## Possible Fix Option 2
```diff
+__declspec(guard(nocf))
FARPROC __stdcall Hook_GetProcAddress(HMODULE p_module, LPCSTR p_name) {
```

My main concern with this fix is whether other compilers (MinGW?)  support this non-standard language extension. 

### Steps to reproduce

1. scons platform=windows arch=x86_64 target=editor ccflags=/guard:cf linkflags=/GUARD:CF
2. Run Godot executable
3. Observe immediate crash, exit code is -1073740791 (STATUS_STACK_BUFFER_OVERRUN)

